The paper deals with a machine learning problem (lasso) and proposes a method for solving it efficiently when the dictionary is too large to fit into memory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of feedback to adapt the sequence of problems to the instance presented, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses datasets that involve image processing (cs.CV) and information theory (cs.IT), which further support the possibility of these sub-categories.
